00:00:47.579 --> 00:00:51.780
who was a nephrologist and an
epidemiologist, and he really introduced

00:00:51.780 --> 00:00:58.890
me to the field of kidney disease and to
transplantation, and really inspired me

00:00:58.890 --> 00:01:06.570
to want to do more in the transplant
world. We want to be able to improve

00:01:06.570 --> 00:01:11.670
equity in access to transplantation. As
an epidemiologist I'm striving for

00:01:11.670 --> 00:01:15.930
trying to collect better data to report
on these differences with the hope that

00:01:15.930 --> 00:01:20.310
eventually there are no differences in
access to transplantation and there's

00:01:20.310 --> 00:01:25.520
equality in transplant access across the
country. Emory Transplant Center is

00:01:25.520 --> 00:01:32.299
phenomenal and I feel so lucky that I am
working here alongside some of the best

00:01:32.299 --> 00:01:39.750
surgeons and nephrologists and others.
I think I want my legacy to be just that

00:01:39.750 --> 00:01:47.250
I made some difference in people's lives.
